==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phrygian cap
<hw>Phryg"i*an cap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A close-fitting cap
represented in Greek art as worn by Orientals, assumed to have been
conical in shape. It has been adopted in modern art as the so-called
<altname>liberty cap</altname>, or <altname>cap of
liberty</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phthalate</ent>⟦br⟧
